THREE men have been arrested in connection with a robbery involving a taxi in Edinburgh this morning.
The incident is alleged to have happened in the city’s Moat Terrace at 5am.
Locals reported a heavy police presence in nearby Slateford Road.
 
@RadioForthNews pic.twitter.com/OPxfQkXcfM

A police spokesman said: “Police Scotland can confirm that we received a report of a street robbery in Moat Terrace at around 5am this morning.
“As a result, three males have been arrested in connection with the incident.”Police added that the incident in Moat Terrace is “ongoing”.
